The project aims to contribute to the development of a common policy for the consolidation of a high level of uniformity in the Union, as the coordination between the organizations is supported at the same time, The project is designed to support the coordination between the bodies working in the field of police cooperation, access to and exchange of information, efficient and secure information and communication systems at the MIA, in line with Regulation (EU) No 515/2014 of the European Parliament and Council. The scope of the project includes:
 - reliable and uninterrupted operation through the follow-up support of the integrated radio-communication system of the MIA according to the TETRA standard;
  - The follow-up support of the technical and software tools for the maintenance of the integrity and support of the N.SIS components

The project is designed to upgrade one of the national databases, expand its capabilities, and include it in international data exchange. It will also be possible to select the two other national databases for data exchange. The result of the project is to be achieved:
 - Improvement of the functioning and reliability of the IBIS system, enlargement of its functionalities by including automated audit of the traces going through the cursula and the international exchange of ballistic information within the framework of the Interpol database - IBIN;
-Increasing the capacity of the National DNA database by including profiles of registered persons and automating the DNA profiling of persons with police registration;
- Improvement of the efficiency of the AFIS system in processing fingerprints and traces and their identification.

The project is designed to achieve a high degree of rigor within the Union, through a strengthening of the institutional capacity to prevent and combat trafficking and organized crime, in accordance with Regulation (EU) No. 513/2014 of the European Parliament and the Council. The specific results are:
- delivered imports;
 - delivered IT equipment and software;
- delivered specialized equipment and machinery for counteracting cross-border, tajik and organized crime.

With the implementation of the project, the project will continue to provide for the establishment of unified leadership and coordination of forces and resources according to the situation, the organization and conduct of local and localized police operations, and the implementation of timely and appropriate measures to counteract cross-border crime and illegal migration.  The following results are implied:
 - Improved efficiency in managing local and local police operations on EU external borders;
 - Increasing the efficiency of the fight against cross-border crime and illegal migration;
 -Improving the strength and sustainability of the system and the developed TETRA system for modern functional capabilities coupled with state-of-the-art technological solutions.

The project is for the purpose of improving the capacity of the FSS-MWR to prevent incidents involving improvised explosive devices for terrorist targets and to increase the ability to respond to crises and terrorist attacks. The project foresees delivery of equipment for protection against terrorist bombing and improvement of the physical and chemical research on chemical materials and technical elements, as well as the implementation of construction and installation works for the construction of a computerized training and firing center for the training of specialized units of the MIA, in order to improve the capacity of the forces to respond to terrorist attacks, to fight against terrorism and organized crime. The specific objectives of the project are:
- Delivered specialized equipment in the field of protection against terrorist bombings;
 - Establishment of a computerized training and firing center for the training of specialized units of the Ministry of Internal Affairs;
- Specialized equipment for physico-chemical examination of explosives and blast components was delivered; - Specialized training for improving the capacity of IDP personnel was carried out

The development and modernization of the NTCs and Regional Operations Centers through the creation of basic infrastructure for emergency response, including the extension of the TETRA radio coverage system for the optimization of the communication environment with interaction on protection structures in the area of European Critical Infrastructure (ECI) facilities and on the population. The specific objectives of the project are:
- The consolidation of interfaces and new functionalities of the NLC, the NLC to the RDDBZN, the District Fire Safety and Protection Services, and the Specialized Operations Centers (SOC) at the RDDBZN;
 - Ensure conditions for timely assessment and collection of informed management decisions in the event of a fire safety event;
 - Enhancement of interoperability between the protection structures and the EKI; - Updating and upgrading of the new functional capabilities of the TETRA system.

In order to improve the administrative and operational capacity to protect critical infrastructure and related national and regional government facilities, an integrated management system (IMS) based on proprietary software has been developed and implemented. The system will collect and process information on those objects as well as use it in the implementation of State Fire Marshall, Preventive Action, and Disaster Protection Act (DPA) activities. The following activities are envisioned for the generation and implementation of the IMS in the SDPD, SDPD, and SDPSA:
- Delivering the necessary hardware and system software with the necessary licenses to build an integrated management system (IMS);
- Establishing interoperability through the Internet;
 - Training the attendants to use the system;
- Activities to implement the system;
- Measures for publicity and visualization.                                                                                                          
  The following results are obtained:
 - The protection of the national and European critical infrastructure is assembled;
-EMIS for gathering and processing information on designated critical infrastructures developed and implemented; - Trained staff from the SDPHS on the system.

According to the Strategy for National Security (NS) of the Republic of Bulgaria, protection of the population and critical infrastructure during crises, disasters, accidents, catastrophes and other risks and disasters is defined as a vital interest. Proactive, preventive measures for protection and enhancement of the strength and resilience of critical infrastructure /in general/ and strategic facilities, from the value of the NS /in particular/ imply the generation and maintenance of goodwill of knowledge and expertise in DANS (the task force in this project). Following an adequate response to the needs and assessment of the increasing role and importance for the NS of the critical infrastructure /strategic objects/ this project foresees the execution of activities "structured" in 2 modules: "Training for trainers" including 2 key activities and several sub-activities and "Training in the field of protection of critical infrastructure, within the framework of the European Partnership and national expertise" including several sub-activities. The following results will be achieved in the implementation of the project:
 - To provide adequate professional training and qualifications for service members and to achieve a high level of national advocacy;
 - Overemphasis on the ability and skills of those serving with the counter-awareness and data protection needs of strategic assets and critical infrastructure;
- Introducing and implementing public-private partnerships when providing assistance to strategic asset managers and corporate citizenship activities, analyzing and assessing risks and creating corporate security; - Increasingly improving specific administrative capacities in the field of public administration. Capacitet in the sphere of counteraction to new emerging risks and patches for counter-recognition and informational integrity of critical infrastructure and strategic assets.

The failure to neutralize the pre-predispositions associated with terrorism, radicalization, and the expansion of aggressive extremism depends on an unstable social situation and requires a different system of coordinated initiatives and expert skills.The key element for comprehending the results of these processes is the early work of not only the law enforcement agencies, but also of all those involved in these processes - national institutions and servants with the right of contact with vulnerable and radicalized communities and groups. To grasp the priority objectives for fighting terrorism on EU soil, the NCTC to DANS was established in 2014 with the PIC as an interagency structure performing the function of a single national platform for collecting and processing information on the identification of persons and organizations involved in terrorism, operating in an unclassified mode and providing coordinated management of national information resources.The project aims to improve the national counterterrorism system by streamlining the work of the NCTC and the specialized directorate at DANS through strengthening the administrative capacity of its staff.                                                              The results of the project are reported:
 - The technical security of the National Counterterrorism Center at DANS for producing analyses for the development of radicalization in Bulgaria;
  - Selected exchange of information between government and civil society partners on radicalization processes.

