The operational and intervention services of the State Border Police carry out activities to counteract and investigate crimes committed in the Border Zone, at the checkpoints and in the territory of the Republic of Bulgaria. Most of the crimes investigated are of a trans-boundary nature and the negative consequences of the crime affect two or more countries. In this context, ensuring timely engagement with partner services in neighboring countries is key to establishing measures for addressing crime. Joint operations involving the services of two or more neighboring countries are an effective way to counteract crime, as the entire crime group is comprehended. Within the framework of these operations, information is exchanged and verified, in most cases through operational means. Some of these methods are observation of persons and means of transportation, vehicle tracking, and address verification and monitoring. The quality of the information obtained depends to a full extent on the technical equipment available, and the ability of the service providers to react adequately and prevent negative consequences is directly dependent on the availability of a secure channel for the exchange of information.This is essential for carrying out operations in areas with limited coverage of mobile operators. As such, this technical equipment would be useless or of minimal effect, unless it was installed with a superior tool that would make the service providers more comfortable in carrying out their tasks. The mass use of vehicles in the MIA system, as well as those used by the intervention unit, is well recognized and in this context equipping them with additional equipment, which can be used for operational purposes with little added durability. In order to enhance the efficiency of law enforcement operations, the delivered technical equipment should be installed in new vehicles similar to the ones used on a large scale.
Results:
- Improvement of the efficiency of the work of the operational and disruptive organizations in the DGPD;
- Approved the technical capacity of the DGPU for effective operational and intervention activities;
- Delivered specialized equipment for operational and intelligence activities to counter crime.

