The project is designed to provide training in risk analysis and assessment in order to improve the strength and protection of strategic assets that are part of the country's critical infrastructure. The project foresees unified training for personnel in strategic facilities and activities that are part of the critical infrastructure, as the project will also include DANS personnel. The training will include 13 separate trainings, which will involve representatives of the relevant sectors of strategic objects and activities.
The target group of the project are:
- Servants of DANS, engaged with counter-intelligence and information protection of strategic objects from the importance of national sigurnost;
- DANS servants trained in a preparatory project financed by the Vatreshnaya Sigurnost (Third Party Integrity) Foundation;
- Owners or representatives of owners and operators of national and European critical infrastructure in the country;
- Other representatives/officials/friends who are entrusted with implementing strategic actions of importance for the country's national security;
- Representatives of firms directly engaged in ensuring the continuity of services provided by strategic facilities and enterprises engaged in strategic activities.
Resultati:
To increase the professional qualifications of the servants to understand the high level of protection of national assets as strategic and part of the national infrastructure.

